      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BAYHARA (2) won well two back over 1931m here before heading to Ascot most recently and being outclassed over 1800m. Back to a more suitable race today and the rise to 2100m is no issue. Maps beautifully with Faithfull in the saddle and she can bounce back to winning ways. HARD QUESTIONS (5) was very good last start over 1600m after producing some good efforts over this distance prior. Getting back out to this course and distance can see him raise the bar again and he looks a leading chance on what he produced last time out. BOMBAY STYLE (1) was solid over 1850m at Dongara last time out as a 20-1 chance. Rates highly on the back of that effort and drops slightly in weight here. Can feature in the finish. BUTTERFLYROCK (3) can improve sharply getting out to a more suitable trip today. KENTUCKY BLUE (4) is racing in good order and if he handles the rise in trip, he'll be right in this.",
